{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3246515,"name":"Daniel","username":"daniel.y","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/bcef8e/{size}.png","created_at":"2023-10-28T06:18:24.247Z","cooked":"<p>We are using the pathplanner 2023-4.2, in the example shown, our robot should just rotate 180 degrees like the photo below.</p>
<p><div class="lightbox-wrapper"><a class="lightbox" href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/4/0/40952de03581be214f485b3b351071960d99ee83.png" data-download-href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/40952de03581be214f485b3b351071960d99ee83" title="image"><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/4/0/40952de03581be214f485b3b351071960d99ee83_2_690x454.png" alt="image" data-base62-sha1="9dkaJiOUISYLTBIMUizo2jwtsk3" width="690" height="454" srcset="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/4/0/40952de03581be214f485b3b351071960d99ee83_2_690x454.png, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/4/0/40952de03581be214f485b3b351071960d99ee83.png 1.5x, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/4/0/40952de03581be214f485b3b351071960d99ee83.png 2x" data-dominant-color="2B2C34"><div class="meta"><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#far-image"></use></svg><span class="filename">image</span><span class="informations">895×589 11.8 KB</span><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#discourse-expand"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>
<p>However our robot rotates more than the degrees and kind of rotates back and forth to its final point. (it is pretty inconsistent and has errors of roughly +/- 5 drgs)</p>
<p>On top of that, translation has shown to also be an issue. We have tuned both the rotation an translation pids and they have shown little no no difference. Pathplanner believes we are driving to this position:</p>
<p>(I cannot add a second embedded image, however it is just a straight line)</p>
<p>However in reality it goes much further</p>
<p>We have tried small (0.25)-extremely large pid values for each. We also see if we add a second way point in between to reach our target rotation earlier, it does reach it at that point, however it continues to uncontrollably rotate as it reaches the end point.</p>
<p>What could be going wrong? Is the PID tuning the wrong approach? We are using the SwerveAutoBuilder. Thank you for any and all help.</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2023-10-28T06:18:24.247Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":399,"reads":205,"readers_count":204,"score":2051.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":443272,"topic_slug":"pathplanners-rotation-is-always-off","display_username":"Daniel","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/4/0/40952de03581be214f485b3b351071960d99ee83.png","internal":true,"reflection":false,"clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":60279,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/pathplanners-rotation-is-always-off/443272/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3246528,"name":"Elliot Scher","username":"Gandagorn","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/gandagorn/{size}/267112_2.png","created_at":"2023-10-28T09:12:49.402Z","cooked":"<p>Can you share your code?</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2023-10-28T09:12:49.402Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":181,"readers_count":180,"score":41.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":443272,"topic_slug":"pathplanners-rotation-is-always-off","display_username":"Elliot Scher","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":49423,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"2815A (19-23) | 190M (23...)"},"post_url":"/t/pathplanners-rotation-is-always-off/443272/2","custom_user_title":"2815A (19-23) | 190M (23...)","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3246591,"name":"Jp","username":"AndromedaHelix","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/andromedahelix/{size}/175921_2.png","created_at":"2023-10-28T18:16:17.986Z","cooked":"<p>Has it worked with just a straight path? No rotation at all, just a 1-2m straight path?</p>
<p>Without reading your code, I recommend checking the following aspects of your robot:</p>
<ul>
<li>The odometry works fine. Create a Field2D object and a SwerveDriveOdometry, and just feed it the positions and angles of each module accordingly. Publish the Field2D to SmartDashboard and move it in teleop to see if the odometry makes sense. For us, this made us notice that our kinematics was wrong, as moving forwards made the odometry think the robot was moving sideways up. Also helps to ensure your gyro is correct.</li>
<li>Check you gyro’s output. Make sure you are working in degrees (or the unit you want, but make sure it makes sense with every part of your code)</li>
<li>Characterizing your robot might help the path planning process.</li>
<li>Make sure your unit conversions are correct i.e from falcon - degrees/meters and to degrees/meters - falcon, etc with your swerve motors.</li>
<li>Test the code with a 1m path. Move the swerve in auto and make it follow said trajectory, then manually measure the distance the robot has moved and compare it with the theoretical value. This can help you tune your PIDs and also will improve if using feedforward through your robot characterization</li>
</ul>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2023-10-28T18:17:33.946Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":7,"reads":164,"readers_count":163,"score":102.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":443272,"topic_slug":"pathplanners-rotation-is-always-off","display_username":"Jp","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":51954,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Head of programming Team 6647"},"post_url":"/t/pathplanners-rotation-is-always-off/443272/3","custom_user_title":"Head of programming Team 6647","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":2}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3246664,"name":"Daniel","username":"daniel.y","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/bcef8e/{size}.png","created_at":"2023-10-28T23:39:33.778Z","cooked":"<pre><code class="lang-auto">// Auto Stuff
